headline.main: EAST AND WEST VIE IN CAPITAL ON WAR; Diplomats of China and Australia Press Pleas for Concentration on Japan MME. CHIANG TOUR A HELP Canberra's Foreign Minister Arrives Soon -- Many in Congress Receptive

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, March 1 -- A major diplomatic struggle, which may affect the length of the war, is being fought in Washington.
abstract: Chinese-Australian conviction of need for Allied concentration against Japan discussed
